description:
This competition-style reality series features amateur Canadian cooks as they work to create and share their innovative, favourite personal recipes with the country.
Each one of the episodes features a different food category with a weekly winner being selected as the finalist.
The finalists' recipes will be available across the country as a President's ChoiceÃ‚Â® product, available in select Loblaw Companies Limited stores and they will receive $25,000.
Weekly winners then move on to compete in the series finale for the grand prize of $250,000.
In the week leading up to the finale, Canadians will be able to join the fun and vote for their favourite.




Recipe To Riches Canada - Season 3, Episode 1




Desserts

On the premiere episode: a bob-sledder from Calgary AB, a farm girl from Penetanguishene, ON and an aspiring actor from Port Coquitlam, BC, compete to find out whose dessert will be on grocery store shelves across the country this weekend - and win a prize of $25,000.




Original Air Date: 26-Feb-2014
